definition.value: Zwitterionic form of agaritine.
A 3-oxoacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of acetoacetyl-CoA.
Tetraanion of coenzyme A.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of acetyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
A  guanidinium ion that is the conjugate acid of blasticidin S.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-leucine residues.
Dianion of hydroxyacetone phosphate.
A multi-methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-oxopristanoyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of succinyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid OH groups.
Trication of (+)-bornyl diphosphate.
Conjugate base of (+)-dihydrokaempferol.
Conjugate acid of (-)-ephedrine.
Conjugate base of (-)-ureidoglycolic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of ent-kaur-16-en-19-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of ent-7alpha-hydroxykaur-16-en-19-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A ribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion that is the trianion of adenosine 5'-triphosphate arising from deprotonation of three of the four free triphosphate OH groups.

A member of the class of  hydroxyisoflavans that is (R)-isoflavan substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2' and 4' , a  3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl group at position 3' and a 2,2-dimethyl-2H-pyran group across positions 7 and 8 respectively.
Zwitterionic form of clavaminic acid.
Zwitterionic form of dihydroclavaminic acid.
Zwitterionic form of proclavaminic acid.
Zwitterionic form of deoxyamidinoproclavaminic acid.

An amino acid zwitterion obtained from N(2)-(2-carboxyethyl)-L-arginine by the removal of a proton for both of the carboxy groups and the addition of a proton to the alpha-amino group and to the guanidyl group.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of glycine.
The dicarboxylate anion of protoporphyrin, obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups.
Dicarboxylate anion of protoporphyrinogen.
An octacarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of all eight carboxy groups of uroporphyrinogen III.
Tetracarboxylate anion of coproporphyrinogen III.
A hydroxyaurone that is aurone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 4' respectively.
A triply-charged organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of presqualene diphosphate.
Tetraanion of (1-hydroxycyclohexyl)acetyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of (2S,3S)-3-hydroxy-2-methylbutanoyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
The tetraanion of a (2R)-2-methylacyl-CoA compound.
The tetraanion of a (2S)-2-methylacyl-CoA compound.

Tetraanion of (S)-3-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups.
A acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of (3S)-3-carboxy-3-hydroxypropanoyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxy functions.
The tetraanion of an (S)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA compound.
The tetraanion of an (R)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA compound.
